data.name: maxSmoothTextBox.ToolTip
data.value:
Works like a framerate limiter. The value should be the refresh rate of your screen.
Can not be lower than 25. Entering lower values or empty spaces will reset the setting to the default value (60).

data.name: memPoolBox.ToolTip
data.value:
Allocates graphics memory in megabytes to texture streaming. 2048 minimum is recommended for the texture pack.
'Infinite'= Poolsize limit will be removed. Useful for in-game texture dumping and debugging.

data.name: texelBox.ToolTip
data.value:
Increases self-shadowing amount. Higher shadow quality setting will improve shadow coverage application.
'High'= May cause some shadow banding artifacts. 'Insane'= This will render much better shadows on character models, but will result in shadow banding artifacts.

data.name: physxBox.ToolTip
data.value:
Demanding feature!
Uses CPU for PhysX instructions (because this machine doesn't use a NVIDIA graphics card) - EXTREMELY demanding. Breakable tiles, realistic paper simulation, advanced smoke effects.
